<P>
Cineplex Odeon Corp.: The Toronto-based film distributor reported a 
second-quarter loss of $39 million, contrasted with a profit of $7 million a 
year ago. Revenue totaled $149 million, up 2%. The results were hurt by a 
since-resolved dispute with "a major distributor," a writeoff of $7 million 
after a decision to abandon a U.S. limited partnership deal and $1 million in 
fees associated with the creation of a special directors committee to review 
any proposals to acquire the corporation. 
</P>
