<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bodies of two Southern California men have been recovered from the wreckage 
of a private plane that crashed Aug. 6 south of Mammoth Lakes. Fresno County 
sheriff's deputies were notified by two hikers over the weekend that they had 
found the wreckage of the single-engine Piper Cherokee in the Pioneer Basin 
area north of Edison Lake. The bodies of the pilot, Redwan Abouhamed, 29, of 
Hawthorne, and a passenger, John Lazar, 29, of Inglewood, were found in the 
burned wreckage. Authorities said it appeared that Abouhamed took the wrong 
corridor through the mountains and was attempting an emergency landing when the 
plane clipped a boulder, crashed and burst into flames. 
