<P>
WOMAN HURT AS SHE IS EJECTED FROM TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Garden Grove woman was injured Monday when she was bounced onto the Garden 
Grove Freeway from the bed of a pickup truck, the California Highway Patrol 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Gail Penner, 26, was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange with cuts and chest 
pains after the 4:30 p.m. mishap on the westbound freeway near the Glassell 
Street crossing in Orange. Penner was reported in stable condition Monday night 
after being admitted for observation, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Penner had been trying to hold down a mattress and box spring in the pickup 
bed, the CHP said. The driver of the truck was Joseph Delpozzo, 25, of 
Westminster. 
</P>
