<P>
BRIEFCASE: EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Irvine Sensors Corp. reported a net loss of $252,400 for its third quarter, 
ending July 2, compared to a loss of $286,700 for the period last year. Revenue 
rose 21% to $822,300 from $680,100. The loss for the nine-month period totaled 
$708,900, compared to a loss of $666,500 for the period in fiscal 1988. Revenue 
increased slightly to $2.2 million from $2.18 million. Irvine Sensors, with 
headquarters in Costa Mesa, develops infrared devices and computer electronics 
for military and commercial systems. 
