<P>
SEPULVEDA TUNNEL TO BE CLOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sepulveda Boulevard Tunnel under Mulholland Drive will be shut down from 
Aug. 19 to Sept. 30 so that the roadway can be reconstructed, two Los Angeles 
city councilmen announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Councilmen Zev Yaroslavsky and Marvin Braude said the closure is expected to 
cause additional congestion on the San Diego Freeway and other highways linking 
the San Fernando Valley with Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
California Department of Transportation officials said the roadway must be 
lowered. They said past resurfacing has raised the street to a point that tall 
vehicles have begun to scrape the tunnel. 
</P>
<P>
The officials said complete closure of Sepulveda between Rimerton Road and 
Royal Hills Drive is needed to ensure public safety. 
</P>
</TEXT>
