</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
J. C. Penney Co. Inc. said today that improved sales in its fashion apparel 
business helped it post a 21.2% profit increase in the second quarter, while 
earnings doubled for another retailer, Dayton Hudson Corp. 
</P>
<P>
The Dallas-based Penney reported that it earned $98 million, or 74 cents per 
share, in the three months ended July 29, compared to $81 million, or 61 cents 
a share, a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Second-quarter revenue rose 5.1% to $3.51 billion from $3.34 billion. 
</P>
<P>
From Minneapolis, Dayton Hudson said it earned a record $56 million, or 72 
cents a share, in the three months ended July 29, up from $28 million, or 34 
cents a share, a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Second-quarter revenue increased 15% to $3.10 billion from $2.69 billion a year 
ago. 
</P>
